Annex - The Brazilian Electric System Green Transition seen from a Dependency perspective v1.1

Rafael da Costa

2024-08-28

This Research Briefing Annex contains all data used in the text The Brazilian Electric System Green Transition seen from a Dependency perspective presented to the organisation of the Workshop on Green energy transitions and global disruption: The (un)just transition to Net Zero, to be held at the University of Manchester, UK on 11-13 September 2024.

This version contains only raw datasets. Some calculations used in the paper are still missing.

Authors contact: Rafael.Da-Silva-Da-costa@warwick.ac.uk

Warning: To access Brazilian federal government open data links provided here you must first setup a VPN with a Brazilian IP mask.

Data on electricity distribution per Brazilian municipalities

Table 1 - GDP, Total Population and Energy Distribution Company per Municipality:

  • This dataset contains more observations (6857) than there are Brazilian municipalities (5572). Since more than one energy distribution company serves certain municipalities, they generate more than one observation.

  • The intention was to identify the energy distributions controller to highlight the concentration existing in the Brazilian Electricity market.

Complete dataset:

Sources: Instituto Brasileiro de Geografia e Estatstica - IBGE, Municipalities Gross Domestic Product, retrieved 28 August 2024 from https://ftp.ibge.gov.br/Pib_Municipios/2021/base/base_de_dados_2010_2021_xlsx.zip; Agncia Nacional de Energia Eltrica - Aneel, Reports Portal, retrieved 28 August 2024 from https://www2.aneel.gov.br/relatoriosrig/(S(gcwd12tr2undw15hdx3vkbjv))/relatorio.aspx?folder=sfe&report=DistribuidoradecadaMunicipio

Table 5 - Brazilian Wind Tech Imports

To identify Brazilian Wind Tech imports the research used the Mercosul Common Nomenclature, which is the standard registry used in Brazil to single out import and export goods.According to this standard registry, wind tech imports fall under the number 8502 - Wind-power Generating Sets.

Complete dataset:

Source: Ministrio do Desenvolvimento, Indstria e Comrcio Exterior - MDIC, Comexstat, retrieved 28 August 2024 from https://balanca.economia.gov.br/balanca/bd/comexstat-bd/mun/IMP_COMPLETA_MUN.zip

Table 6 - Brazilian Solar Tech Imports

To identify Brazilian Wind Tech imports the research used the Mercosul Common Nomenclature, which is the standard registry used in Brazil to single out import and export goods.According to this standard registry, wind tech imports fall under the number 8541 - Solar-power Generating Sets.

Source: Ministrio do Desenvolvimento, Indstria e Comrcio Exterior - MDIC, Comexstat, retrieved 28 August 2024 from https://balanca.economia.gov.br/balanca/bd/comexstat-bd/mun/IMP_COMPLETA_MUN.zip
